  "text": ". This effect suggested that once the leaves reach the maximum N concentration, the plant tend to increase size and biomass instead of increasing N concentration. The N fertiliser efficiency based on the N increase with respect to the non-fertilised treatment was z45% up to the recommended rate (170 kg N ha ), but decreased to 31% for the 220 kg N ha À1 treatment. The recommended rate is in agreement with previous recommendations made for maize crop in this region (Gabriel, Alonso-Ayuso,García-Gonz alez, Hontoria, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
